Program: Discovery
Title: An earth made for life - part one
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryzq
Last Broadcast Date: 14 June 2005
A series of programmes looking at the origins of complex life on earth. The first programme looks at the tenacity of life and how life became ever more complex, at around 2 billion years ago. Early earth was a very different place, where the only life existing in slime. Then the Cambrian explosion happened. Show less